Annual cumulative exposure to
radiation may exceed safety standards in parts of Fukushima
prefecture outside the 20-kilometer evacuation zone around  Tokyo 
electric Power Co.â€™s crippled nuclear reactors, the Asahi
newspaper  reported .  People living in certain areas in the city of Minami Soma
in Fukushima, north of Tokyo, will receive 23.8 millisieverts of
annual cumulative exposure at current radiation levels,
exceeding the yearly safety limit of 20 millisieverts, the Asahi
reported, citing a report by the science ministry.  Areas in the city of Date would receive 20.8 millisieverts,
the newspaper report said. Calls to the science
